Subgroup Analysis: Vulnerability indicators

pre<-read.csv("/Users/kevinkuehn/Documents/UWEXP/COVID/phase.csv")

pre$sd_BDI2[pre$Q_BDI2>mean(pre$Q_BDI2)+sd(pre$Q_BDI2)]<-1
pre$sd_BDI2[pre$Q_BDI2<=mean(pre$Q_BDI2)+sd(pre$Q_BSI2)]<-0

ID<-pre[pre$sd_BDI2 == 1,"PID"]

UWEXP$high_BDI2<-NA
UWEXP$high_BDI2[UWEXP$PID %in% ID=="TRUE"]<-1
UWEXP$high_BDI2[UWEXP$PID %in% ID=="FALSE"]<-0

mod1<-lme(fixed = as.numeric(PHQ4) ~ rank+as.factor(high_BDI2),
         data = UWEXP,
         random = ~ rank+as.factor(high_BDI2) | PID, na.action=na.omit)

Testing and plotting heterogeneity of responses

UWEXP$PID<-as.factor(UWEXP$PID)

vars<-c("PID", "rank", "Anxious")
UWEXP2<-UWEXP[vars]
UWEXP2<-na.omit(UWEXP2)

UWEXP2$Model.F.Res <- residuals(fm2) #extracts the residuals and places them in a new column in our original data table
UWEXP2$Abs.Model.F.Res <-abs(UWEXP2$Model.F.Res) #creates a new column with the absolute value of the residuals
UWEXP2$Model.F.Res2 <- UWEXP2$Abs.Model.F.Res^2 #squares the absolute values of the residuals to provide the more robust estimate
Levene.Model.F <- lm(Model.F.Res2 ~ PID, data=UWEXP2) #ANOVA of the squared residuals
anova(Levene.Model.F) #displays the results
